  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Somalia: Strengthening the Capacity of the Justice Sector to Prosecute Terrorism Offenses</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To strengthen the capacity of personnel from the Attorney General&#x2019;s Office (AGO), the Judiciary and the Bar Association to deal with serious criminal offenses. 2) To facilitate an exposure visit to Kenya for key justice sector personnel to discuss lessons learned and good practices in the defense, prosecution and administration of terrorism trials.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Personnel from justice institutions in South Central Somalia.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to increase the capacity of the civilian justice system to prosecute terrorism offenses in accordance with international fair trial standards, while also minimizing the security risk posed by accused terrorists to Somali society.</narrative>
  </description>
